race.comment: SHYSTAR (11) comes through two very good fillies' races from winter, running well in both, including a 1.2 length third behind subsequent 1000 Guineas winner Ole Dancer. Jumpouts in preparation for the return have been delightful. MISSAPPREHEND (7) is from a top stable and was in the market for a race at Caulfield on Wednesday, but has been saved for this, which looks a good lead. VENETIAN CHOICE (14) comes through the same Ballarat maiden that supplied the filly who would have started a hot favourite here - JESSICA RABBIT - and while well beaten it looked a hot race. She'll have come on from that, too. MISS ELLANEOUS (6) was tested in some good races last prep, finishing second in the Elvstroem Classic and fifth in a Listed race at her final run before a spell, so she'll find this a lot more to her liking.
